commit.message:
Move df-prod entry in mmil.html

This is to match its position in set.mm.
Add ntrivcvgmul to mmil.html
add ntrivcvgtail to mmil.html
add ntrivcvgfvn0 to mmil.html

Update uzind4i in iset.mm

Copied from set.mm to reflect removal of an unnecessary hypothesis
there.  Update the one proof which had used uzind4i in iset.mm.

Add ntrivcvgap0 to iset.mm

This is ntrivcvgn0 from set.mm with not equal changed to apart.  The
proof is the set.mm proof with not equal changed to apart in each step.

Add elabd to iset.mm

Copied without change from set.mm

Add ntrivcvgap to iset.mm

This is ntrivcvg from set.mm with not equal changed to apart.  The proof
needs intuitionizing in various steps but is basically the set.mm proof.

Add adantl3r and friends to iset.mm

This is adantl3r , ad4ant13 , ad4ant14 , ad4ant23 , ad4ant24 , adantl4r ,
ad5ant12 , ad5ant13 , ad5ant14 , ad5ant15 , ad5ant23 , ad5ant24 ,
ad5ant25 , adantl5r , and adantl6r .  Copied without change from set.mm.

Add prodfdivap to iset.mm

This is prodfdiv from set.mm with changes as noted.  The proof needs a
fair bit of intuitionizing but is basically the set.mm proof.

Add spvv and chvarvv to iset.mm

Stated as in set.mm.  The proof of chvarvv is the same as set.mm, the
spvv proof is just from spv .  Remove statements about axiom usage, as
this would require iset.mm-specific investigation and the iset.mm axioms
are moderately different from the set.mm ones.

Add prodfrecap to iset.mm

This is prodfrec from set.mm with not equal changed to apart.  The proof
needs intuitionizing in various places but is basically the set.mm
proof.

Add prodfap0 to iset.mm

This is prodfn0 from set.mm with not equal changed to apart.  The proof
needs intuitionizing in several places but is basically the set.mm proof.

Add prodfclim1 to iset.mm

Stated as in set.mm.  The proof needs a bit of intuitionizing but is
basically the set.mm proof.

Add prodf1f to iset.mm

Stated as in set.mm.  The proof needs some intuitionizing for
differences in seq theorems but is basically the set.mm proof.

Add prodf1 to iset.mm

Stated as in set.mm.  The proof needs intuitionizing for differences in
seq related theorems but is basically the set.mm proof.

Add prod3fmul to iset.mm

This is prodfmul from set.mm with additional conditions on the sequence
(as in many of our theorems where we treat a finite sequence as the
initial part of an infinite sequence).

Add df-proddc to iset.mm

This is based on the set.mm df-prod in much the same way that df-sumdc
is based on df-sum from set.mm.
